gh its query execution path.\n\n## Functions Implementation (promql/functions.go)\nThe FunctionCall type (line 39-60) defines the signature for function implementations that process evaluated arguments. The FunctionCalls map (line 2151-2154+) contains the runtime implementations of PromQL functions. There are also special function registries like AnchoredSafeFunctions (line 2254-2259) and SmoothedSafeFunctions (line 2265-2270) that define which functions support these modifiers.\n\n## Features Registration (promql/parser/features.go)\nThe RegisterFeatures method (line 21-58) registers PromQL language features with the feature registry, including keywords (like 'anchored' and 'smoothed' for extended range selectors), operators, aggregators, and functions. This enables feature flags for experimental features controlled by EnableExperimentalFunctions option.\n\n## Supporting Components\n- promql/parser/printer.go: Provides Tree() and other printing utilities for AST nodes\n- promql/parser/prettier.go: Handles formatting and pretty-printing of AST nodes\n- promql/value.go: Defines the Value interface for query result values\n\n## Pipeline Flow\nThe parsing and validation pipeline flows as follows: NewParser creates a promQLParser -> ParseExpr calls parseExpr on a new low-level parser -> parseExpr calls parseGenerated which uses the lexer to tokenize and the yacc parser to parse -> checkAST recursively validates the resulting AST for type correctness -> the validated AST is returned to the caller and eventually passed to Engine for execution."
